config: Increase BUILD_MAX_EXTDRIVE from 16 to 36

Raise the maximum number of drives per type (floppy, hard disk, CD-ROM) to 36.
This provides additional headroom for systems with many drives, such as multiple
hard disks, CD-ROMs, or virtual floppies. All arrays dimensioned by
BUILD_MAX_EXTDRIVE expand accordingly, consuming negligible additional memory.

Signed-off-by: Mike Banon <mikebdp2@gmail.com>
---
 src/config.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/config.h b/src/config.h
index 16952eb7..5700450a 100644
--- a/src/config.h
+++ b/src/config.h
@@ -20,7 +20,7 @@
 #define BUILD_MIN_HIGHTABLE (256*1024)
 #define BUILD_MAX_HIGHTABLE (16*1024*1024)
 // Largest supported externaly facing drive id
-#define BUILD_MAX_EXTDRIVE 16
+#define BUILD_MAX_EXTDRIVE 36
 // Number of bytes the smbios may be and still live in the f-segment
 #define BUILD_MAX_SMBIOS_FSEG     600
 // Maximum number of bytes the mptable may be and still be copied to f-segment
-- 
